  '8ce2ff8c-1d95-4c6e-b751-0a8032095788',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$rust_sys: Taming Comptime with Zig's Allocators$escape$,
  $escape$When working with comptime in rust_sys, you can use Zig's allocators to handle memory management. Zig's allocators provide a way to allocate memory at comptime, eliminating the need for runtime allocations. To use Zig's allocators, you can import the `zig_std_allocator` crate and use the `std.heap` module. For example, you can use the `std.heap.page_allocator` to allocate memory at comptime: `let allocator = std.heap.page_allocator; let ptr = allocator.alloc(u8, 10);`. This approach ensures that memory is allocated at compile-time, reducing runtime overhead.$escape$,
  $escape$let allocator = std.heap.page_allocator; let ptr = allocator.alloc(u8, 10);$escape$,
  $escape$rust$escape$,
